Well, you're considered great if you can read a pitcher's mind just by looking at his face.

68
00:05:22,820 --> 00:05:24,500
Hey, what are you doing there ?

69
00:05:25,510 --> 00:05:27,200
Hey, popcorn.
Do you want some ?

70
00:05:28,200 --> 00:05:29,510
You're going to buy me some ?

71
00:05:29,510 --> 00:05:30,250
Of course.

72
00:05:30,250 --> 00:05:31,300
Thank you very much.

73
00:05:31,300 --> 00:05:32,000
Sure.

74
00:05:55,500 --> 00:05:56,290
Kunimi.

75
00:05:58,820 --> 00:06:00,760
You didn't force yourself to come with me, right ?

76
00:06:04,490 --> 00:06:05,400
It was an obligation.

77
00:06:06,700 --> 00:06:07,460
Obligation.

78
00:06:07,950 --> 00:06:11,330
Don't put on an act. 
I know you're having fun.

79
00:06:11,330 --> 00:06:14,400
Hey, how old are you ? How old ?!

80
00:06:14,400 --> 00:06:18,200
There's no way I could enjoy
 being with a cheeky kid like you !

81
00:06:18,200 --> 00:06:19,400
Shut up and eat !

82
00:06:23,120 --> 00:06:23,930
Huh ?

83
00:06:25,610 --> 00:06:28,500
That show of anger is really an expression of love.

84
00:06:33,350 --> 00:06:35,250
I'm happy that it's
 an amusement park.

85
00:06:35,250 --> 00:06:36,050
What ?

86
00:06:36,050 --> 00:06:38,000
Instead of the folk dance, I mean.

87
00:06:40,340 --> 00:06:42,600
Weekdays are great.
 It's not crowded.

88
00:06:43,300 --> 00:06:44,300
Yeah.

89
00:07:08,660 --> 00:07:09,510
Koga.

90
00:07:09,510 --> 00:07:10,000
Yes ?

91
00:07:12,060 --> 00:07:14,870
The carp here are so gluttonous.

92
00:07:17,740 --> 00:07:18,930
You're right.

93
00:07:23,800 --> 00:07:24,430
Hey.

94
00:07:29,710 --> 00:07:32,120
You're high school 
students, aren't you ?

95
00:07:32,120 --> 00:07:33,400
Yes.

96
00:07:33,990 --> 00:07:35,820
What about school ?

97
00:07:35,820 --> 00:07:38,700
We had a cultural festival on Sunday, so we have an off day today instead.

98
00:07:39,930 --> 00:07:41,130
You're off today ?

99
00:07:41,130 --> 00:07:42,130
Yes.

100
00:07:42,130 --> 00:07:43,050
Fine, then.

101
00:07:43,050 --> 00:07:44,540
Let's go there now.

102
00:07:44,540 --> 00:07:46,700
The surprise house ? Don't be
 surprised by your own face, okay ?

103
00:07:46,700 --> 00:07:48,300
That's mean. 
That goes for you, too.

104
00:07:48,300 --> 00:07:50,030
But really, some of those
 make you look scary.

105
00:07:50,030 --> 00:07:54,000
Nowadays, high school kids should hold hands. You two should, too.

106
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:55,000
Right ?

107
00:07:59,250 --> 00:08:02,580
Amusement park. It's so joyful.
 Amusement park.

108
00:08:03,380 --> 00:08:04,930
What was that about ?

109
00:08:05,690 --> 00:08:06,640
You know ?

110
00:08:06,640 --> 00:08:07,300
Yeah.

111
00:08:10,380 --> 00:08:11,990
Let go of me.

112
00:08:11,990 --> 00:08:15,300
Don't be bashful. 
We're just holding hands.

113
00:08:15,300 --> 00:08:16,650
I'm not being bashful.

114
00:08:21,640 --> 00:08:22,580
Ryutarou.

115
00:08:23,560 --> 00:08:24,300
You want one ?

116
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:28,880
I don't want one. 
Just finish it already.

117
00:08:28,880 --> 00:08:31,990
Oh, man.
 My clothes got sticky, too !




118
00:08:33,160 --> 00:08:34,220
You two.

119
00:08:34,220 --> 00:08:35,690
What happened to school ?

120
00:08:35,690 --> 00:08:36,500
What ?

121
00:08:40,120 --> 00:08:43,240
Well, we have a day off  
because of the cultural festival.

122
00:08:43,240 --> 00:08:44,270
Right ?

123
00:08:46,820 --> 00:08:49,300
One boy ticket and 
one girl ticket, please.

124
00:08:49,300 --> 00:08:51,170
You mean one adult
 and one child, right ?

125
00:08:51,170 --> 00:08:53,420
Why are you so flustered ?

126
00:08:53,420 --> 00:08:54,590
Shut up !

127
00:08:56,700 --> 00:09:01,600
Leaves turning red. Walking while holding hands. The autumn sky.

128
00:09:01,600 --> 00:09:03,000
That's a great haiku.

129
00:09:04,830 --> 00:09:05,830
What is that about ?

130
00:09:31,900 --> 00:09:33,800
Hey, what's your next whim ?

131
00:09:32,150 --> 00:09:39,680
Jumping over the puddles one by one...

132
00:09:37,400 --> 00:09:39,900
I was just trying to think 
of one. My next whim is...

133
00:09:39,680 --> 00:09:46,650
...I want to get past a hardship like that.

134
00:09:39,900 --> 00:09:41,760
Umm, what's the next one ?

135
00:09:41,760 --> 00:09:42,580
It's #23.

136
00:09:42,580 --> 00:09:44,160
You've been counting, Kunimi ?

137
00:09:44,160 --> 00:09:44,900
I'm just kidding.

138
00:09:47,650 --> 00:09:55,200
Like you, I run up the pedestrian bridge...

139
00:09:49,660 --> 00:09:50,840
Is that it ?

140
00:09:51,840 --> 00:09:53,150
No.

141
00:09:53,150 --> 00:09:56,120
I'm saving that one for last.

142
00:09:55,200 --> 00:10:03,150
...keeping up with the sunny sky, I want to feel courageous.

143
00:09:57,250 --> 00:09:57,990
Let's go.

144
00:10:03,150 --> 00:10:09,650
"How does he keep such a nice facial expression ?"

145
00:10:03,400 --> 00:10:05,700
I guess we're riding that one, too ?

146
00:10:09,650 --> 00:10:18,300
I thought with frustration, when I met you.

147
00:10:12,550 --> 00:10:15,190
It was a mirror, but you
 were acting like it was real.

148
00:10:17,400 --> 00:10:18,400
Kunimi.

149
00:10:18,300 --> 00:10:21,900
"I'm definitely glad we met."

150
00:10:18,400 --> 00:10:19,110
Yeah ?

151
00:10:21,900 --> 00:10:26,000
Let's stay strong and move forward.

152
00:10:24,610 --> 00:10:25,660
Hmm. 

153
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:33,700
When I'm by myself I notice, that, beyond this dazzling feeling...

154
00:10:27,800 --> 00:10:29,410
Hey, it's well-made.

155
00:10:33,700 --> 00:10:41,500
...yesterday, today, and tomorrow, there are more and more smiles.

156
00:10:41,500 --> 00:10:48,500
Just by looking at you, see ? My eyes will look kinder.

157
00:10:43,460 --> 00:10:44,800
Hey, Koga.

158
00:10:46,120 --> 00:10:47,940
This one looks interesting, too.

159
00:10:48,510 --> 00:10:49,440
Let's go.

160
00:10:50,990 --> 00:10:52,000
Sure.

161
00:10:59,670 --> 00:11:00,990
Wait up, Kunimi.

162
00:11:25,670 --> 00:11:27,120
Where are you, Kunimi ?

163
00:11:37,970 --> 00:11:39,900
Aim for the Koushien

164
00:11:38,360 --> 00:11:39,970


165
00:11:45,180 --> 00:11:47,850
Aim for the Koushien

166
00:11:45,300 --> 00:11:46,960


167
