I can't find him.

169
00:13:10,600 --> 00:13:13,200
What happened to your boyfriend ?

170
00:13:14,200 --> 00:13:15,270
You two lost each other ?

171
00:13:15,270 --> 00:13:16,600
Yes.

172
00:13:16,600 --> 00:13:19,800
That's why I told 
you to hold hands.

173
00:13:23,130 --> 00:13:26,220
A minor cross-up
 leads to the end of love.

174
00:13:29,840 --> 00:13:30,800
Sorry about that.

175
00:13:36,710 --> 00:13:38,300
I'm telling you.

176
00:13:38,300 --> 00:13:45,900
The lost child is a long-haired, lecherous-looking high school boy.

177
00:13:45,900 --> 00:13:48,120
He's totally useless without me.

178
00:13:48,120 --> 00:13:50,230
He's aimless and helpless.

179
00:13:50,230 --> 00:13:52,440
Really, he's such a handful.

180
00:14:22,990 --> 00:14:24,930
Why are you making such a face ?

181
00:14:27,510 --> 00:14:29,700
I was afraid that 
you'd left me behind.

182
00:14:30,660 --> 00:14:32,750
That maybe I asked for too much.

183
00:14:32,750 --> 00:14:35,860
I promised to spend the day with you.

184
00:14:35,860 --> 00:14:37,110
Honestly ?

185
00:14:37,110 --> 00:14:40,230
Honestly. You should have confidence in yourself.

186
00:14:42,500 --> 00:14:45,400
Ring Toss

187
00:14:42,500 --> 00:14:45,400
Three rings per game, 200 yen

188
00:14:42,500 --> 00:14:45,400
The prize of the ring toss must
be completely inside the ring.

189
00:14:46,420 --> 00:14:47,990
Here are the three rings.

190
00:14:56,160 --> 00:14:56,990
That one !

191
00:15:02,330 --> 00:15:03,080
All right.

192
00:15:03,960 --> 00:15:05,710
I wanted to come to
the amusement park.

193
00:15:06,240 --> 00:15:09,360
At an amusement park, we can go back to feeling like children.

194
00:15:09,360 --> 00:15:13,350
I thought I'd be able
to see your everyday self.

195
00:15:19,170 --> 00:15:22,800
Well, it's a date today.
I guess I'm a little tense.

196
00:15:23,440 --> 00:15:24,300
A date ?

197
00:15:25,250 --> 00:15:26,870
Don't repeat what I said.

198
00:15:31,290 --> 00:15:33,080
You're being bashful.

199
00:15:37,900 --> 00:15:39,700
Peerless

200
00:15:41,870 --> 00:15:43,290
You can throw it away.

201
00:15:43,290 --> 00:15:45,650
Why ? I wanted this one.

202
00:15:45,650 --> 00:15:46,970
You've got to be kidding.

203
00:15:46,970 --> 00:15:48,060
I'm being honest.

204
00:15:50,500 --> 00:15:52,370
Well, what's next ?

205
00:15:52,820 --> 00:15:56,920
Shall we go for the one we've saved ?

206
00:15:56,920 --> 00:15:57,620
Sure.

207
00:16:21,580 --> 00:16:23,190
Wow, it's a great view !

208
00:16:26,490 --> 00:16:27,510
I guess so.

209
00:16:33,180 --> 00:16:34,490
Look, Kunimi !

210
00:16:35,620 --> 00:16:36,660
I'll see it later.

211
00:16:37,360 --> 00:16:40,200
Are you afraid of heights ?

212
00:16:41,540 --> 00:16:42,480
A little.

213
00:16:48,700 --> 00:16:51,750
But you said you
 wanted to ride this.

214
00:16:51,750 --> 00:16:54,560
You looked like you wanted to.

215
00:16:59,130 --> 00:17:01,510
Don't move ! 
It's losing balance !

216
00:17:03,130 --> 00:17:06,050
When I first met you, it was spring.

217
00:17:08,330 --> 00:17:10,000
Were you able to burn it ?

218
00:17:11,410 --> 00:17:13,270
Kunimi Hiro.

219
00:17:15,800 --> 00:17:19,040
I'm Koga Haruka, the manager for the Senkawa High School Baseball Club.

220
00:17:32,590 --> 00:17:34,580
It's coming up soon.

221
00:17:34,580 --> 00:17:35,340
What is ?

222
00:17:43,130 --> 00:17:44,250
Look, Kunimi !

223
00:17:52,940 --> 00:17:55,550
To tell the truth, I wanted us to see this together.

224
00:17:57,750 --> 00:17:58,510
What is it ?

225
00:18:27,380 --> 00:18:29,100
You wanted juice ?

226
00:18:30,250 --> 00:18:31,300
Yeah.

227
00:18:57,200 --> 00:18:57,960
Thanks.

228
00:19:01,990 --> 00:19:02,940
It feels good.

229
00:19:16,250 --> 00:19:17,080
Sorry about that.

230
00:19:27,760 --> 00:19:28,890
Since when ?

231
00:19:28,890 --> 00:19:31,180
It's been like this since
 I woke up this morning.

232
00:19:31,180 --> 00:19:35,010
That's stupid ! You should
 have called me and canceled !

233
00:19:35,010 --> 00:19:37,200
No way ! 
It would be such a waste.

234
00:19:37,200 --> 00:19:39,440
You're paying for everything today.

235
00:19:39,440 --> 00:19:40,950
You're the daughter
 of a company president.

236
00:19:40,950 --> 00:19:42,600
There's no need to be stingy !

237
00:19:44,240 --> 00:19:47,480
I've been looking forward to this, since yesterday.

238
00:19:52,650 --> 00:19:53,780
We're going home.

239
00:19:54,680 --> 00:19:56,550
You promised to 
spend the day with me.

240
00:19:59,660 --> 00:20:02,400
Today isn't the only off day.

241
00:20:02,400 --> 00:20:05,150
If you don't mind splitting the tab, I'll go out with you anytime.

242
00:20:08,910 --> 00:20:10,480
Really ?

243
00:20:11,030 --> 00:20:11,500
Yeah.

244
00:20:12,040 --> 00:20:13,680
Then we'll go home.

245
00:20:26,200 --> 00:20:30,670
In five years, you'll be cuter, even if not as cute as Koga.

246
00:20:48,110 --> 00:20:49,160
It's hot !

247
00:20:50,940 --> 00:20:54,200
What did you do that for ?!

248
00:20:54,200 --> 00:20:56,700
It made a mark on my cheek !

249
00:20:56,700 --> 00:20:57,460
Oh, well.

250
00:21:00,470 --> 00:21:01,690
It's hot.

251
00:21:09,240 --> 00:21:10,130
Koga ?

252
00:21:24,000 --> 00:21:25,200
Oh, pardon me.

253
00:21:27,960 --> 00:21:28,580
Oh.

254
00:21:32,550 --> 00:21:34,380
Could you take a photo of us ?

255
00:21:41,300 --> 00:21:42,300
Today, too.

256
00:21:42,300 --> 00:21:44,650
Romance begins at the amusement park.

257
00:21:44,650 --> 00:21:48,200
And I make happiness.

258
00:21:48,200 --> 00:21:49,250
Too many syllables.

259
00:21:50,200 --> 00:21:51,200
Say cheese.

260
00:21:55,170 --> 00:21:57,400
You shouldn't take
 a photo of us like this.

261
00:21:57,400 --> 00:21:59,990
It's to commemorate our first date.

262
00:21:59,990 --> 00:22:01,150
Oh, well.

263
00:22:01,150 --> 00:22:03,410
I look forward to spending time with you.

